com.github.jonathanxd.iutils.grabber

Class AbstractGrabber<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.jonathanxd.iutils.grabber.AbstractGrabber<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of elements to store.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Grabber<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArrayGrabber, ListGrabber, StringCharGrabber

    public abstract class AbstractGrabber<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Grabber<T>
    Abstract implementation of Grabber. This implementation stores blacklisted elements by index in a boolean blacklist array. Implementations must override get(int) method that is like a List.get(int) method. This method gets elements by index.

      • getBlacklistedIndexes

        protected boolean[] getBlacklistedIndexes()
        Gets all blacklisted indexes. Implementation that override this method must take care about getWhitelistIndex(). The index can be easily recalculated calling calculateWhitelistIndex(). This array must be the original blacklisted index array, not a copy.
        Returns:
        Blacklisted indexes.
